cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new approach to Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) using Capsule Network. It also involves comparing the performance of different GAN architectures on various datasets. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it deals with image generation and uses MNIST and Fashion-MNIST datasets. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in AI research. Furthermore, it may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks in the GAN architecture. Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) as it deals with generating images.
